# Expo only exposes EXPO_PUBLIC_-prefixed vars to app code — same idea as
# Vite's VITE_ prefix in apps/web.

# Same Spotify client ID already used by apps/web (client IDs aren't
# environment-specific — one client ID, multiple redirect URIs registered
# against it). Unlike the other vars here, this one is also read at
# `expo prebuild` time by app.config.js (the @wwdrew/expo-spotify-sdk plugin
# bakes it into the native project) — so this file needs to exist with a
# real value *before* running `expo prebuild`/`eas build`, not just before
# `expo start`.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=

# A custom URI scheme for this app (see app.config.js's "scheme" and its
# @wwdrew/expo-spotify-sdk plugin config), used as the auth redirect target
# instead of a web URL. Register `listensync://spotify-auth` with the
# Spotify app too, alongside the existing web redirect URIs — note the
# native SDK's authenticateAsync() doesn't actually take this as a runtime
# argument; the real redirect URI is baked in by app.config.js's plugin
# config at prebuild time. This var is just for registering the same string
# in Spotify's dashboard.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI=listensync://spotify-auth

# Same relay — wss:// in production (the Render URL). For local dev, this
# is NOT reached from the same machine/process the way a browser tab would
# reach it — this runs on a separate device/emulator, so "127.0.0.1" means
# that device's own loopback, not your dev machine. Use your machine's real
# LAN IP instead (e.g. ws://192.168.1.42:8787) — works from the Android
# emulator, a real device on the same WiFi, AND (since the relay listens on
# all interfaces by default) doesn't break anything. The Android-emulator-
# only special alias `10.0.2.2` also works but is a dead end for real-device
# testing later, so prefer the LAN IP from the start. Also used for the
# Spotify native login's token-swap POST (spotify/auth.ts) — if this isn't
# reachable, that fails too, not just room sync.
EXPO_PUBLIC_RELAY_URL=ws://192.168.1.42:8787

# The deployed web app's URL, launched in a Chrome Custom Tab for the Apple
# Music path (see src/screens/AppleMusicScreen.tsx — sidesteps both the
# native MusicKit framework's EAS/provisioning entitlement gap AND a real
# bug where an embedded WebView can't complete MusicKit JS's popup-based
# auth at all, see MOBILE_V2_PLAN.md's "Apple Music pivot #2"). Production:
# the Vercel URL. Local dev: same LAN-IP reasoning as the relay above — also
# needs apps/web/vite.config.ts's dev server bound to all interfaces
# (`host: true`), not just 127.0.0.1, or the LAN IP won't reach it at all.
EXPO_PUBLIC_WEB_APP_URL=http://192.168.1.42:8888
